    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-11-02T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-11-02T17:00:00-05:00" n="997"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d997">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.922/99: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Siam</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Neville</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-11-02T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 2, 1937—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>25. Your No. 31, November 1, 5 p.m. Department agrees to phrase “without
                    prejudice to settlement according to international law”.</p>
                <p>With reference to proposal drafted by Minister of Foreign Affairs this Government
                    prefers provision concerning movable property in Article 1 already agreed upon.
                    As to immovable property see Department’s telegram No. 24 of November 1.</p>
                <p>As soon as Department is informed that you have reached agreement on immovable
                    property Department will send you telegram confirming its understanding of final
                    text of treaty, protocol and exchange of notes.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
